dcterms:creator: T. Wei
dcterms:description: The FastICA algorithm is one of the most popular iterative algorithms in the domain of linear independent component analysis, focusing on the relationship between demixing vectors, local optimizers of the contrast function, and fixed points of the FastICA algorithm.
dcterms:title: FastICA algorithm

dcterms:description: The bimodal distribution used in this paper consists of a mixture of two Gaussian distributions.
dcterms:title: Bimodal distribution

dcterms:description: The generalized Gaussian density function with parameter α, zero mean and unit variance is given by fα(x) = αβα/(2Γ(1/α)) exp(−(βα|x|)α), where α is a positive parameter that controls the distributions exponential rate of decay.
dcterms:title: Generalized Gaussian distribution

dcterms:description: The empirical FastICA function is derived from the FastICA algorithm and is used to estimate the demixing vectors based on empirical data.
dcterms:title: Empirical FastICA function
